reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good and dependable
reviews.reviewText: This is a very good charger. Definitely worth the money. I would definitely recommend this to anyone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works perfectly for iPhone 13pro
reviews.reviewText: The title says it all. It charges extremely fast and the phone doesn’t display any “unsupported accessory” message. The USB-A port might deliver less power than the USB-C one, since when I connect my iPhone with the original cable and a wireless charger in the USB-A port at the same time, the wireless charger does not work properly, as if the charger was a low-powered one, it has to be connected on its own.Other than that, it can charge two devices without a hiccup when you use a cable for both, so no biggie.Also, for the price, the two pack was a bargain, great chargers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for price
reviews.reviewText: It charges my devices quickly. However, if you have two plugged into the thing at once each device won't charge as fast (but that is expected). I have noticed that it seems to produce a high pitched whine while charging which is annoying as I charge my devices while I go to sleep.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Has both USB-A and USB-c output ports
reviews.reviewText: The charger seems to be of high quality and works fine. The power rating is a bit misleading to me. It is sold as a 20W charger. However, in the 5 volt mode, the max rating is 3A, or 15W. It is only using the USB-c port in the 9V or 12V mode that it is rated at 20W. The USB-A port at 9V or 12V is rated at 18W.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I need a USB-C wall charger to connect and charge my drone. I bought this 3-pack product and figured I’d give the other 2 chargers to my kids, great decision. This wall charger is perfect for charging all USB-C AND original USB products. I use it for my drone, my kids use it for their phones, headsets, gaming consoles, and anything electronic that needs charging. The size is perfect, not to big, not too small to lose it. Very sturdy, and mobile. The price was excellent, considering 3 chargers came in the package. I’ll definitely do business with this company again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this product this works super well for me or my guess in my Airbnb because I know depending on whatever charger you have it's either a USB or it's a USB c. I find that this works really well because some people who have different ends on their Chargers might need one or the other option additionally those who have iPhones versus Androids might also just have the USBC as a post to the USB C and so I find that this has worked really well in fact one of my tenants in my Airbnb enjoyed these so well that they took it when they left so it's very quick and easy and I definitely recommend. The one thing that I would say is if there is a way to improve on the product that would be to collapse the plug into the wall so that it doesn't stick out when you're not using it and if you want to travel with it that would make it a little bit easier

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to charge an Oculus Quest but the results were.. questionable. It charges but I'm not sure that it's 20w, I would need to do more research to determine if it's actually 20w. It seems a bit slower but ultimately, it did its job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super plug base at a reasonble price
reviews.reviewText: I used these while traveling internationally and they worked out wonderfully. Easy and had the proper outlets for my devices. Allen
